## Core objects

### Semantic Node

The canonical unit of meaning. One concept, pattern, daemon, invariant, protocol, or operational insight.

Schema: [`schema/semantic_node.schema.json`](schema/semantic_node.schema.json)

**Five-field minimal form** (required for canonization):

```yaml
name: string
invariant: string
neighbors: [string]
failure_mode: string
transfer: string
```

If a concept cannot survive compression into these five fields, it is not yet stable enough for canonization.

### Semantic Edge

A typed, weighted relationship between two nodes.

Schema: [`schema/semantic_edge.schema.json`](schema/semantic_edge.schema.json)

Valid relation types: `supports | opposes | refines | generalizes | instantiates | maps_to | predicts | guards | compresses | rehydrates`

### Transfer Rule

Describes how a concept moves across substrates. Cross-domain mapping is permitted only when the preserved invariant is named.

Schema: [`schema/transfer_rule.schema.json`](schema/transfer_rule.schema.json)

